    content: `<p>Lighting is the most underestimated element of wedding styling. Couples spend hours choosing flowers, centrepieces, and colour palettes, yet the lighting can make or break how all of those elements actually look and feel in the space. The right lighting creates warmth, romance, and atmosphere. The wrong lighting — harsh overhead fluorescents — flattens everything. Here is how Melbourne couples are using lighting to transform their wedding venues.</p>

<h2>Fairy Light Curtains: The Signature Wedding Backdrop</h2>

<p>Our <a href="/hire/fairy-light-curtain">Fairy Light Curtain</a> is one of our most hired items across all wedding types, and for good reason. Hundreds of warm white LED lights cascading from ceiling to floor create a wall of soft, twinkling light that works as a ceremony backdrop, bridal table feature, or photo wall. The curtain measures 3 metres wide and 2.4 metres tall — large enough to create real impact without overwhelming a space.</p>

<p>Fairy light curtains photograph beautifully at every stage of the day. In daylight, they add a subtle sparkle. As the afternoon light fades, they begin to glow more prominently. By evening, they become a luminous backdrop that flatters skin tones and creates depth in photos. Position one behind your <a href="/hire/backdrop-draping-set">Backdrop Draping Set</a> for a layered effect that combines soft fabric with warm light — the combination is absolutely stunning.</p>

<h2>Festoon Lights: Outdoor Wedding Essentials</h2>

<p><a href="/hire/festoon-light-string">Festoon Light Strings</a> are the signature lighting element for outdoor Melbourne weddings. Their warm Edison-style bulbs create an inviting, relaxed atmosphere that signals celebration. String them overhead between trees, posts, or purpose-built frames to define your reception space and create a canopy of golden light.</p>

<p>Festoon lights are particularly effective at outdoor venues across <a href="/event-styling/werribee">Werribee</a>, <a href="/event-styling/point-cook">Point Cook</a>, and the Mornington Peninsula, where the open sky needs a visual ceiling to make the dining space feel contained and intimate. Each of our festoon strings is 10 metres long and can be linked together for larger installations. The warm glow they cast as the sun sets creates that magical transition from daytime celebration to evening party.</p>

<h2>Neon Signs and Letter Light-Ups</h2>

<p>Feature lighting adds personality and creates focal points throughout your venue. Our <a href="/hire/neon-sign-custom-text">Custom Neon Signs</a> in warm white or coloured LED create a modern, personalised statement. Popular choices include your married surname, wedding date, "Better Together," or "Til Death Do Us Party." Mount your neon sign on a greenery wall, above the bar, or behind the dance floor for maximum impact.</p>

<p><a href="/hire/gold-letter-light-up">Gold Letter Light-Ups</a> make a bold statement spelling out initials, names, or meaningful words. Their warm bulb glow creates a vintage, marquee-style effect that works across rustic, modern, and glamorous wedding themes. Position them behind the bridal table, beside the dance floor, or at the entrance for a wow-factor moment that guests notice immediately.</p>

<h2>Candles and Ambient Lighting</h2>

<p>No wedding lighting plan is complete without candles. Pillar candles in glass hurricanes at varying heights on each table create intimate pools of warm light that make the dining experience feel special. Taper candles in metallic holders add height and elegance. Scattered tea lights fill gaps between other table elements with gentle, flickering warmth.</p>

<p>For ceremony aisles, lanterns with candles create a beautiful pathway of light for evening ceremonies. Clusters of candles around the base of your <a href="/hire/rustic-arch-backdrop">Rustic Arch Backdrop</a> or <a href="/hire/round-moongate-arch">Moongate Arch</a> add romantic warmth. Combined with our <a href="/hire/ceiling-draping-package">Ceiling Draping Package</a> overhead and fairy lights behind the bridal table, the overall effect is a reception space bathed in layers of warm, golden light.</p>

<h2>Planning Your Wedding Lighting</h2>

<p>When planning your lighting, consider these practical tips:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Visit your venue at night:</strong> Understand what the space looks like once the sun goes down. Identify which existing lights can be dimmed or switched off.</li>
<li><strong>Layer your lighting:</strong> Combine overhead festoons or draping lights, mid-level feature lights like neon signs, and table-level candles for a rich, atmospheric effect.</li>
<li><strong>Consider power access:</strong> Our team checks power point locations during the venue assessment to ensure all lighting can be safely installed.</li>
<li><strong>Warm tones only:</strong> Cool white LEDs and blue-toned lights are unflattering. Stick to warm whites and golden tones for a universally romantic effect.</li>
</ul>

<p>At iDo. Events, our lighting installations are delivered, set up, and removed by our team across Melbourne. Whether you need a single fairy light curtain or a complete lighting transformation, we have the <a href="/hire">hire pieces</a> and expertise to create the perfect atmosphere. <a href="/quote">Request a free quote</a> and let us light up your wedding.</p>`,
